Scotland’s free schools continue to exhibit academic excellence, and this has persisted in 2018 with another year of outstanding exam results, underpinned by individual and shared success in sports, arts, music and other community initiatives.
These schools, represented by The Scottish Council of Independent Schools, have more than 30,000 students across Scotland and work hard to deliver the very best school experience to both students and parents.
Free schools aim to prepare their students for further and higher education, their chosen careers and their position as world citizens.
As an educational institution that can design and implement a tailor-made school curriculum, we see that modern languages are constantly a popular and in demand elective subject in schools.
Nelson Mandela said, “If you speak to a man in a language he understands, his words reach his head.
If you speak to him in his own language, the words reach his heart.”
This is a powerful reminder that we can’t just stick to English when we want to build relationships and trust with people from other countries.
From this year’s exam results, we see that languages are at the top of the table with the highest pass rates from free schools.
